80.1	The_Hedgehog_and_the_Fox	The Hedgehog and the Fox	"The Hedgehog and the Fox" is an essay by the liberal philosopher Isaiah Berlin. It was one of Berlin's most popular essays with the general public. Berlin himself said of the essay: "I never meant it very seriously. I meant it as a kind of enjoyable intellectual game, but it was taken seriously. Every classification throws light on something."	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/01/Hedgehogandfox.JPG/200px-Hedgehogandfox.JPG
